records.addlTxt:
John Vaughn sworn to interpret.
State files an Amended Information charging 3 cts. Possess Cocaine, contrary to Section 961.41(3g)(c) of the Wisconsin Statutes.  
No contest pleas to the amended charges.  Convicted.   Sentences are withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years, on each count, to run concurrent to each other.   Conditions of probation are:
1) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
2) AODA assessment and follow through;
3) Full-time employment/job search;
4) Spend ninety (90) days in the Manitowoc County Jail, under the Huber Law, sixty (60) days to be served up front, commencing on or before 04-30-15 by 6:00 p.m. and thirty (30) days to be stayed and to be imposed at the agent's discretion and upon order of the Court;
5) Maintain absolute sobriety;
6) Submit to random drug screens and pay for same;
7) Pay $450.00 for buy money;
8) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights.
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.  
Court Order for Intoxicated Driver Assessment and Driver Safety Plan.  
Minutes.
